  "prompt": "What are some Yu-Gi-Oh! Apps?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, there are several Yu-Gi-Oh! apps that fans and players might find useful. Here are some of them:\n\n1. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Links**: This app allows players to experience the Yu-Gi-Oh! trading card game in a mobile format. It features various characters from the series, simplified gameplay mechanics suitable for mobile, and online multiplayer dueling.\n\n2. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Neuron**: An official companion app that provides tools for players, including a card database, deck-building features, and rules reference. It\u2019s designed to assist players in organizing their decks and checking card rulings.\n\n3. **Dueling Book**: While primarily a web-based platform, many players access this tool on mobile devices. It allows players to create and duel with their own decks online, serving as a platform for casual and competitive play.\n\n4. **YGOPRO (YGOPRO Percy)**: This is an unofficial simulation app that allows players to duel online against others. While it\u2019s primarily PC-based, there are mobile versions available through various forks of the project.\n\n5. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Card Database Apps**: There are several third-party apps that provide comprehensive databases for Yu-Gi-Oh! cards. Apps like \"Yu-Gi-Oh! Card Maker\" allow fans to create custom cards, while others facilitate searching and tracking cards.\n\n6. **Duelist Toolbox**: A mobile app that can help players manage their collections, get information on card prices, and assist with deck-building strategies.\n\n7. **Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG Official Card Game (OCG) Apps**: Depending on your region, there may be official apps tailored for the OCG format, which is popular in Japan.\n\nMake sure to check your app store (Google Play Store or Apple App Store) for availability and the latest versions of these apps, as new tools and updates are frequently released in the Yu-Gi-Oh! community.",
